The Commission of Inquiry into allegations of State Capture, chaired by Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo, will on Monday hear testimonies of staff members in the office of the Minister in the Presidency. Former Chief Director of that ministry, Brent Adrian Simmons is expected to be the first on the stand when the commission resumes at 10 am. Another employee in the office of the Minister in the Presidency, former Chief of Staff, Abednigo Hlungwani is also expected to testify. Last week, the commission looked at issues regarding the Estina Dairy project, with former Free State Department of Agriculture Head of Department,  Peter Mbana Thabethe being the last on the stand. The commission also marked its first anniversary last week. Watch video below, for Peter Thabethe’s testimony at the State Capture Inquiry: 